The paper discusses the generalization of Convolutional Neural Networks to signals defined on more general domains without the action of a translation group. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) as it deals with the development of new architectures for deep learning. Additionally, the paper focuses on image and audio recognition tasks, which are common applications of Computer Vision (cs.CV). The use of graphs and hierarchical clustering also suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of Network Science (cs.NE) or Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper proposes new constructions for convolutional layers, which is a common topic in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
